post_text: We are a mask distribution site for 18 school districts in our area. These masks were donated by the Missouri State Emergency Management Agency for students this school year. Dr. Glass picked them up from our friends at Farmington R-7 School District yesterday so that students in our region will have masks to start the new school year!
shared_text:
Mike Mohundro KFVS
August 19 at 10:04 AM ·

90,000 masks were just delivered for schools in Southeast Missouri.

Cape Girardeau Public School Superintendent Neil Glass picked up the masks which will be distributed to schools in Cape Girardeau, Scott and Bollinger Counties.

These masks will be for students and staff to help them keep safe while in the classrooms to help prevent COVID-19.

post_text: The Cape Girardeau County Public Health Center is hosting immunization clinics in July and August to help families get ready for the new school year. Drive-thru clinics will be held at Arena Park on July 24th and August 8th. There will also be a number of other clinics held at their offices, but you need to make an appointment. Call 573-335-7846 to schedule your appointment. The consent forms and more detailed information about the clinics are available on capetigers.com under District Announcements.

post_text: Good afternoon, families! We wanted to make sure everyone saw this important information from the Cape Girardeau County Public Health Center. Please make note, per the order, students who are 10 years of age and older will need to wear a face covering (if medical conditions allow) in our buildings. If your child has medical needs that prohibit them from wearing a mask, please be sure to share that with your building principal. We greatly appreciate everyone working together to help protect the health and safety of our entire community. Take care and have a great rest of your weekend!

post_text: We are working hard to establish a safe plan to welcome our students back this fall and are putting the finishing touches on plans for in-person summer school. Please know this is not something we are doing alone. We will continue to work with our local health officials to make sure we are following their guidance. We also want our families involved in the process. Look for a survey, soon. Until then, we encourage you to continue stressing the importance of social distancing and being respectful of the health of others with your children. We want a happy and healthy community so we can continue to educate our students.

post_text:
KINDERGARTEN ROUNDUP TIME!

We are hosting Kindergarten Screening July 20 - July 23, 2020. To be eligible for kindergarten, children must turn 5 years of age on or before July 31, 2020.

To participate in this screening, you must have previously enrolled your child in kindergarten at the Central Administration Office. The screening takes approximately 1 hour, and your child should wear sneakers or some type of closed-toe shoe. The screenings will take place at the Central Administration Office, 301 N. Clark St.

Please call 335-1867 to schedule your child’s appointment. No walk-ins will be accepted. Thank you!

It might have been a little different type of celebration for this iconic day, but the show had to go on...no matter what! 🐅 Thanks to the Southeast Missourian for capturing these beautiful photos!

post_text: We have had many people ask about volunteering with our meal program, including delivery to families who cannot come to one of the five elementary sites. Please fill out this volunteer form and share the info with anyone you know who might be interested. We are so thankful for you! 🐅 ❤️🐅
shared_text:
COGNITOFORMS.COM
Volunteer Form for Cape Girardeau Public School Food Distribution

Ruth Ann Orr
March 18 at 4:06 PM ·

For those of you who are wanting to do SOMETHING...here is your perfect opportunity! Please click on the link below and complete this volunteer form. Cape Girardeau Public Schools are needing volunteers for food preparation and distribution during the time they are out.

There are a few "musts": You must come alone. You must be healthy. Finally, you must be able to commit to staying the entire shift. This decreases the risk of food contamination by decreasing the number of people handling the food.

Do not just show up. Volunteers will be contacted by someone from Cape Girardeau Public Schools to tell you when and where to serve.

post_text: We will be providing meals to children 18 and under today at our five elementary schools. Each site will have its own flow of traffic and will begin distributing those meals at 10AM. Please be patient with us as we work to serve our families. This situation is a new one for all of us and we realize it will take teamwork. We are focused on supporting our families and the community as we can, and we are thankful to live in a place full of people who are wanting to do their part, too. We have had a number of people reach out to us to volunteer and we could be calling on you soon to help. Thank you again for BEING what makes our community so SPECIAL. We are all in this together and right now you are helping set the example for our students. #WeareCT
shared_text:
Cape Girardeau Public Schools
March 16 at 5:34 PM ·

IMPORTANT COVID-19 UPDATE: The CGPS Board has voted to close schools Wednesday, March 18, 2020 - Friday, April 3, 2020. We will determine by April 3 if it is appropriate for us to return to school Monday, April 6, 2020. Our families should have received an email with this information this evening. Please be patient with us as we work to determine next steps over the next couple of weeks as we keep student and staff safety in mind. We are going to be providing meals to children, 18 years and younger at our elementary schools from 10AM-noon beginning this Wednesday. These sites will be open Monday - Friday. Please share this information as we are committed to providing every support that we possibly can to our families. Thank you all for your patience with us.

post_text:
We are continuing to thoroughly clean buildings and encourage all of our students, staff members, families and other visitors to practice general germ-prevention measures to help us keep our buildings clean and safe.

Please be sure to:
-Cover your mouth when you cough or sneeze
-Wash hands for at least 20 seconds with soap and warm water
-Avoid touching your face
-Avoid close contact with people who are sick
-Stay home if you are ill, keep children home from school until they are fever-free for 24 hours

To stay well-informed of the latest developments as it relates to COVID-19 and any other important health information, please check the CDC website, regularly: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/cases-in-us.html

post_text: We are so proud of our Charles C. Clippard Elementary Tigers for their second place showing in this NATIONAL competition! #WeareCT
shared_text:
Charles C. Clippard Elementary
February 28 at 3:12 PM ·

Clippard students and teachers celebrated their Imagine Learning Literacy Bowl 2nd place finish in style! We enjoyed a pajama day with popcorn and a movie in the gym. Mr. Bob from Imagine Learning stopped by to present our school with a plaque and $200 gift card. Ms. Tinnin's class won a pizza party for logging the most minutes and Kindergartener Lucas was recognized for having the most individual minutes logged (1,625 minutes!).

Since September, over 13,600 schools; 85,000 classrooms, and nearly 1 million students participated in the competition. We are so proud of our students! A big thanks also goes out to our sponsors for providing popcorn for the whole school! #clippardstrong #clippardcares #weareCT #imaginelearning

post_text: Service before self. So proud of our Jefferson Elementary family! #WeareCT
shared_text:
Jefferson Elementary
February 26 at 9:58 PM ·

🙌🏽💞Today our 1st Grade Students served at The People’s Shelter!!! They packed hygiene kits & snack bags. They also helped Renita Marie Green set up cots and made the beds for some of our friends to sleep on tonight. We learned more about homelessness & how we can help! They wrote some of their happy thoughts to keep in their hearts & minds & then they helped beautify the grounds!!! They also collected food donations from our JE Families for more sack lunches in the future! Thank YOU, for serving our community and allowing us to serve alongside you! #JEserves 💞🙌🏽

Cape Cenral High School Students & Family’s 🧡

Join us this evening during Parent Teacher Conferences for a Job & Resource Fair! Employers such as Walmart, Rhodes 101 and the Census Bureau— just to name a few are here and READY to have you fill out an application and interview you!

Thank you to the entire ABCToday Network for assisting with this event.

post_text: The Air Force JROTC has been extremely busy representing Cape Girardeau Public Schools throughout the state, including a recent trip to Jefferson City for the Student Showcase. The event went very well with cadets engaging with state legislators, school board members from various school districts, and students from other schools. The cadets were able to lead people through several fun, hands-on experiences including a flight simulator, drone simulator, and cyber-security demonstrations. #WeareCT
